# Flutter & Dart Style

## Formatting

Always run `dart format .` before committing. CI enforces this with
`dart format --output=none --set-exit-if-changed .` and will fail if code is
not formatted.

## Folder Structure

Use the **feature-first** folder layout defined in `docs/ProxDroid_Architecture.md §4`.
Every feature lives under `lib/features/<feature>/` with three sub-folders:

```
lib/features/<feature>/
├── data/          # Repository and data-source classes
├── providers/     # Riverpod provider files
└── ui/            # Screens, widgets specific to this feature
```

Shared widgets go in `lib/shared/widgets/`.
Shared constants go in `lib/shared/constants/`.
Core infrastructure (API client, base models, storage) goes in `lib/core/`.

## File Naming Conventions

| File type | Suffix |
|---|---|
| Screen (full-page route widget) | `*_screen.dart` |
| Repository | `*_repository.dart` |
| Riverpod provider file | `*_providers.dart` |
| Riverpod notifier class | `*_notifier.dart` |

## Separation of Concerns

- **Never** put UI code (widgets, BuildContext, theme) in data/repository files.
- **Never** put API calls, Hive access, or business logic in UI files — these belong in repositories and are accessed via providers.
- UI reads Riverpod state; UI never mutates state directly.
